    "title": "Introduction to Array Sorting",
    "content": "Sorting an array involves rearranging its elements in a specific order, typically either in ascending or descending order. There are several algorithms used for sorting, including Bubble Sort, Selection Sort, Insertion Sort, Merge Sort, and Quick Sort."
  },
  {
    "title": "Bubble Sort Algorithm",
    "content": "### Bubble Sort Algorithm
```python
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n-1):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1] :
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
    return arr
```
This algorithm works by repeatedly swapping the adjacent elements if they are in wrong order."
  },
  {
    "title": "Quick Sort Algorithm",
    "content": "### Quick Sort Algorithm
```python
def quick_sort(arr):
    if len(arr) <= 1:
        return arr
    pivot = arr[len(arr) // 2]
    left = [x for x in arr if x < pivot]
    middle = [x for x in arr if x == pivot]
    right = [x for x in arr if x > pivot]
    return quick_sort(left) + middle + quick_sort(right)
```
This algorithm selects a 'pivot' element from the array and partitions the other elements into two sub-arrays, according to whether they are less than or greater than the pivot."
